    "body": "After first look, here's the plan:\r\n\r\n1. Check the component for unused items\r\n2. Try to use `Loader` for `StatusMenu.delegate`. \r\nThis should improve performance significantly, because we usually only see 20-30% of all possible actions.\r\n3. Move `deleteMessageConfirmationDialogComponent` to `Popups`\r\n4. Move `FileDialog` to `Popups`\r\nAccording to profiler, this one seems to be one of the heaviest parts.\r\n5. Create a single instance of `Menu` for the app.\r\nAdd `messageStore` property and access the menu through `Global`\r\n6. Remove `Utils.getContactDetailsAsJson`. \r\nThis data is probably already available at component creation.\r\nAlso check for any other \"backend\" access.\r\n7. Separate `ProfileContextMenu`",
